<item>
            <title>[HBASE-1982] [EC2] handle potentially large and uneven instance startup times</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1982</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The variability in instance start latency may impact a HBase cluster. All the slaves are started with one invocation of ec2-run-instances but not all may come up at once. Handle potentially large and uneven instance startup times through a master configuration option that prevents assignment of user tables until the configured number of region servers are up. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
